title: Bakso
description: Bakso is savory meatball and noodle soup. Also has hard boiled eggs and other potential add-ins like tofu or bok choy.

title: Mi Goreng
description: Mi goreng is a stir-fried noodle dish with a thick and flavorful sauce. You can pick your choice of chicken, beef, shrimp, or all three.

title: Nasi Goreng
description: Nasi goreng is Indonesia's version of fried rice. Packs more flavor you can pick your choice of chicken, beef, shrimp, or all three. Topped with a fried egg.

title: Satay Ayam
description: Satay ayam is a chicken skewer marinated in sweet soy sauce and grilled over a flame. Served with a spicy peanut sauce.

title: Soto
description: Soto is an Indonesian chicken soup with a nice herbal broth and rice noodles, chicken, hard boiled eggs, and other various toppings.

title: Martabak Telur
description: Martabak telur is a savory roti-like fried pancake stuffed with a beef and egg filling. Very popular on the streets of Indonesia.

title: Chicken Kebab
description: Chicken kebabs are cubes of chicken marinated in a blend of herbs and spices, skewered, then grilled.

title: Falafel
description: Falafel is a deep fried ball of chickpeas and other herbs and spices.

title: Shakshuka
description: Shakshuka is a dish with poached eggs in a tomato based sauce. Served with pita bread.

title: Pilaf
description: Pilaf is a rice dish where the rice is cooked in a stock or a broth along with other aromatics.

title: Baklava
description: Baklava is a pastry made with filo dough filled with nuts and held together with honey.

title: Hummus with Vegetables
description: Hummus is a chickpea paste along with other flavorings, served with vegetables to dip it in.
